The problem was, you can sell a company software, but you can=E2=80=99t for=
ce them to use it to its fullest extent. =C2=A0
But what if you owned the company?=C2=A0
After Ento, Chris had caught the industrials bug, and more specifically, he=
 realized that there was an enormous opportunity in advanced manufacturing.=
 It was critically important, fragmented, and the owners of the small shops=
