06-4e58-86a7-6967f949e15f?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepK=
bqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ].=C2=A0
Last week, we defined Vertical Integrators as companies that:=C2=A0
Integrate multiple cutting-edge-but-proven technologies.
Develop significant in-house capabilities across their stack.
Modularize commoditized components while controlling overall system integra=
tion.
Compete directly with incumbents.
Offer products that are better, faster, or cheaper (often all three).
If you haven=E2=80=99t read Part I [ https://substack.com/redirect/63944d9c=
-0406-4e58-86a7-6967f949e15f?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXX=
epKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] yet, you should do that before reading this one. The=
 big takeaway is that =E2=80=9CAggregators won the Internet by leaning as h=
ard to one side of the business model spectrum as possible; Vertical Integr=
ators will win the physical world by leaning as hard to the opposite side a=
s they can.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0
There is a set of problems that are information problems =E2=80=93 they can=
