?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel st=
yle=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">Vertical Integr=
ator</a></strong><span>.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55)=
; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Last week, we de=
fined Vertical Integrators as companies that:&#160;</p><ol style=3D"margin-=
top: 0; padding: 0;"><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;"><p style=3D"box-si=
zing: border-box; color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26p=
x; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;">Integrate multiple cutt=
ing-edge-but-proven technologies.</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px=
;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 1=
6px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;">De=
velop significant in-house capabilities across their stack.</p></li><li sty=
le=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb=
(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom:=
 0; padding-left: 4px;">Modularize commoditized components while controllin=
g overall system integration.</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;"><=
p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px;=
 line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;">Compet=
e directly with incumbents.</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;"><p =
style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; l=
ine-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;">Offer pr=
oducts that are better, faster, or cheaper (often all three).</p></li></ol>=
<p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; mar=
gin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>If you haven&#8217;t read </span><a href=3D"https:/=
/substack.com/redirect/63944d9c-0406-4e58-86a7-6967f949e15f?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXA=
wZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rg=
b(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">Part I</a><span> yet, you shoul=
d do that before reading this one. The big takeaway is that &#8220;</span><=
strong>Aggregators won the Internet by leaning as hard to one side of the b=
usiness model spectrum as possible; Vertical Integrators will win the physi=
cal world by leaning as hard to the opposite side as they can.&#8221;</stro=
ng><span>&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16=
px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">There is a set of problems that=
 are information problems &#8211; they can be solved with software.&#160;</=
p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; m=
argin: 0 0 20px 0;">There is another (much larger) set of problems that are=
 physical problems &#8211; they cannot be solved with software alone. They =
require physical solutions, often augmented by software.&#160;</p><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;"><span>Hadrian is a perfect example to study, both because as it s=
tands, it&#8217;s a textbook Vertical Integrator, but also because it shows=
 how tempting it is to try to use software to solve the problem. Even the f=
ounder of one of the most promising Vertical Integrators turned to software=
 first. When that didn&#8217;t work, he built a </span><em>system</em><span=
> involving hardware, software, and humans. </span></p><p style=3D"color: r=
gb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><s=
pan>As I wrote in that Deep Dive, &#8220;It </span><strong>automates what c=
an be automated</strong><span>, and </span><strong>hires and trains humans =
to do what humans do best</strong><span>, and </span><strong>coordinates al=
l of it with software.&#8221;</strong></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55=
); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>It seems =
to be working. Hadrian is </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/8=
43a7607-9cbd-4392-a442-70eca80fbdc1?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNua=
MZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-deco=
ration: underline;">worth</a><span> roughly $500 million expects to reach $=
30 million in revenue this year as a three-year-old company. </span></p><p =
style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin=
: 0 0 20px 0;">When I started writing Part II, my plan was to leave the Had=
rian example at that: as an example of the fact that software alone can&#82=
17;t fully solve problems in the physical world, that software is not the a=
nswer, as much as founders or investors would like it to be given the relat=
ive ease of building software and the potentially high margins once you do.=
&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height:=
 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">But one of the fun things about sending this es=
say in parts versus all at once is that I got a lot of good feedback after =
Part I that I can use to make this essay smarter and more nuanced than it w=
ould have been otherwise.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font=
-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>One particularly=
 insightful comment came from </span><a href=3D"https://open.substack.com/p=
ub/notboring/p/vertical-integrators?r=3D1ftlg&utm_campaign=3Dcomment-list-s=
hare-cta&utm_medium=3Dweb&comments=3Dtrue&commentId=3D66956816" rel style=
=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">Carter Williams</a=
><span>, who worked for the CTO at Boeing in Phantom Works after doing grad=
uate work on vertical versus horizontal integration at MIT. He pointed out =
that, as with most things, the need for vertical versus horizontal innovati=
on moves in </span><strong>cycles</strong><span>. As he summarized: &#8220;=
Markets go vertical to innovate product, horizontal to reduce cost and scal=
e. Back and forth over a 40-50 year cycle.&#8221;&#160;</span></p><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;">Vertical integration, in other words, is not always the right app=
roach in a given industry. If existing products are &#8220;good enough&#822=
1; for customers, companies compete on the basis of cost, convenience, or c=
ustomization, which favors more modular architectures and horizontal specia=
lization.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; lin=
e-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">If manufacturing were humming in Ameri=
ca, Chris may have been able to build a good business selling software to m=
ake it hum a little more cheaply or faster. But manufacturing in America wa=
sn&#8217;t humming, it was breaking down, so he had to rebuild a new system=
 from scratch. </p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; lin=
e-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Carter&#8217;s comment led me down a r=
abbit hole, and expanded the scope of this essay. We&#8217;re going to need=
 to do it in at least three parts.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, =
55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Today, =
in Part II, we&#8217;re going to focus on one of the most important questio=
ns to ask of any startup &#8211; </span><strong>why now?</strong><span> &#8=
211; at economy scale.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); =
font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Why are we seeing =
more companies &#8211; across industries as diverse as manufacturing, energ=
y, aerospace, defense, mining, and housing &#8211; choose to vertically int=
egrate to create entirely new capabilities instead of simply improving exis=
ting capabilities now?&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-si=
ze: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">The implications are mass=
ive for founders and investors. If you think the existing system simply nee=
ds to be improved, you might want to build or invest in the types of compan=
ies that can improve it.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-=
size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><strong>But if you beli=
eve that we&#8217;re in a moment in which systems need to be rebuilt, then =
you will want to build or invest in a smaller number of Vertical Integrator=
s that can handle as much complexity as is needed to pull their industry in=
to a new and better way of operating.</strong></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54=
, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">As you =
might have guessed, I believe we&#8217;re in one of those moments.&#160;</p=
><h3 class=3D"header-anchor-post" style=3D"--highlight-bg: rgba(var(--color=
