 line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;">New TE=
Ps involve a constellation of multiple new, interrelated technologies that =
aren't yet well understood or standardized.&#160;</p></li><li style=3D"marg=
in: 8px 0 0 32px;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(54, 55, 5=
5); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; paddin=
g-left: 4px;">The full potential of new technology combinations isn't yet k=
nown, requiring experimentation and control over multiple components to ite=
rate quickly.</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;"><p style=3D"box-s=
izing: border-box; color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26=
px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;">There's a lack of esta=
blished supply chains and ecosystems for these new inputs.</p></li></ol><p =
style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin=
: 0 0 20px 0;">Intrepid entrepreneurs will need to vertically integrate to =
figure out how to build the new products the market needs, and the new busi=
ness models to support them, before the rest of the market can come in to i=
mprove processes and modularize inputs in order to bring down costs and imp=
rove performance.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 1=
6px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">It&#8217;s the hard way, but a=
s Chris Power and others have discovered by trying the &#8220;easy&#8221; w=
ay first, it may be the only way to really make a dent in critical physical=
 industries.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-h=
eight: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>To that end, I&#8217;d like to leav=
e you with a </span><strong>hypothesis: if you want to build a Vertical Int=
egrator, now is the time.</strong><span>&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color:=
 rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">=
The first company in each category to vertically integrate enough with a so=
lution that is much cheaper, better, or faster than the incumbent will be w=
ell-positioned to win that category and build a very large business, and it=
 will be difficult for others to displace them.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color:=
 rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">=
<span>There&#8217;s a lot of nuance needed in that statement. The first Ver=
tical Integrator in a category certainly won&#8217;t always be the winner. =
Look at </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/89897e2b-f2f2-44e8-=
b34a-d2ba000189b7?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6=
m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;=
">Katerra</a><span> in housing construction as one example. In fact, the fi=
rst often &#8220;takes the arrows,&#8221; learning lessons that successors =
will incorporate into their models.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(=
54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Just =
launching a Vertical Integrator at the right time isn&#8217;t enough. </p><=
p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; marg=
in: 0 0 20px 0;">The Vertical Integrator needs to combine the new technolog=
ies in just the right way to create a much better solution with structurall=
y superior unit economics, at reasonable scale, on paper to start. It needs=
 to build the team that can turn &#8220;on paper&#8221; into &#8220;in prac=
tice,&#8221; and attract the investors willing to fund the company until it=
 gets to the scale that it can compete (and raise debt or project financing=
 to scale further). It needs to overcome regulatory roadblocks thrown in it=
s way by the incumbents. And it needs a product so much better, cheaper, or=
 faster that customers and partners, used to doing something the old way, a=
re motivated to switch to something new.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54=
, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>I=
t&#8217;s worth remembering that we are not the first generation of intelli=
gent people interested in applying new technology to make better products. =
Read </span><em>Kochland, Titan, Cable Cowboy</em><span> or any number of b=
ooks and biographies on very large companies built at the turn of previous =
TEPs. Many of those companies are still operating, and will fight back vigo=
rously, often attempting to incorporate the same technologies into their pr=
oducts and processes. It will be a battle. </span></p><p style=3D"color: rg=
b(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><sp=
an>But if the Vertical Integrator can pull all of that off &#8211; and ofte=
n much more &#8211; </span><strong>all of those challenges become a moat, a=
nd advantages compound</strong><span>. It becomes very hard to displace a T=
EP&#8217;s first big winners until a new Techno-Economic Paradigm emerges s=
ome time fifty years into the future (or potentially sooner, if the cycles =
speed up).&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 1=
6px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Why that is is a conversation =
for Part III. </p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line=
-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Today, we talked about the theore=
tical and practical </span><strong>Why Now</strong><span> for Vertical Inte=
grators.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">In Part III, we&#8217;ll dive in=
to the specifics: challenges they face, the advantages they might have, wha=
t it takes to build them, and what the implications of all of that might be=
=2E</p><div style=3D"font-size: 16px; l=
ine-height: 26px;"><hr style=3D"backgr=
